property.name: note
property.value:
This event is a little bit complex...but basically, as the glider speed increases, the playhead transitions from sound to sound at a faster pace.
If you look closely at a single "note" in the sequence, there are 6 transition markers - each "step" in the speed change is set to about 20% difference in duration.
The transition markers each have "glider_speed" as a conditional parameter, each subsequent marker mapped to respond to a lower range of speed.
This approach allows us to control the pace of playback from note to note without significantly changing pitch.
